    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    ArrayMaze
    A rectangular maze using an array structure to represent cells and walls in a 2D space.
    Cell
    A cell located within an ArrayMaze.
    Cell.Endpoint
    Describes the role of a cell in the maze: start, end, or none.
    ConnexeApp
    Our entire application, which persists until it is closed.
    ConsoleApp
    Allows users to see/generate/solve Mazes in the terminal with a menu
    ControllerHub
    Receives game controller input, all in one place, using SDL2.
    ControllerHub.State
    All connected controllers with all their currently pressed keys and joystick positions.
    ControllerState
    The state of a controller's buttons and joysticks.
    EfficiencyHUDController
    The HUD controller for the efficiency game mode.
    Endpoints
    Contains both the start and end vertex of a maze to generate.
    FurtivityHUDController
    The HUD controller for the furtivity game mode.
    GameMath
    Various mathematical utilities for game development: mainly interpolation and easing functions.
    GameMode
    A game mode for arcade gameplay.
    GameSession
    An ongoing game in arcade mode; handles player input, game state, and rendering.
    GameStartConfig
    All settings to begin a new arcade game.
    GraphMaze
    A rectangular maze using a graph structure to represent connections between cells, called vertices.
    HUDController
    Base class for every controller managing an arcade HUD.
    IncompatibleMazeException
    Thrown when a maze's topology is incompatible with a particular GameMode.
    InputSystemException
    Thrown when something went wrong with SDL2.
    InvalidVertexException
    Thrown when an invalid vertex is used as an argument in GraphMaze.
    KeyboardHub
    Receives keyboard input from a JavaFX scene, providing the currently pressed keys at any time.
    MainController
    The controller of the main layout (menu bar, and overall ui).
    MazeController
    Controller to display any Maze related operations on the view (creation, editing, solving, etc...)
    MazeEditor
    Class to manage the selection, deletion and addition of walls in the maze.
    MazeEditor.Side
    Four possible directions for the walls of the labyrinth.
    MazeGenerator
    Generates mazes (perfect and not perfect) using various algorithms.
    MazeGenEvent
    A step of a maze generation algorithm, contained in a MazeGenLog.
    MazeGenEvent.Connect
    Two vertices of the maze graph have been connected: they are accessible, and the wall between those two is now broken.
    MazeGenEvent.Disconnect
    Two vertices of the maze graph have been disconnected: they are no longer accessible, and the wall between those two is now present.
    MazeGenEvent.SetEndpoints
    Start and end vertices of the maze graph have been set.
    MazeGenLog
    A sequence of maze generation events describing all steps taken during a maze generation algorithm.
    MazeGenResult
    The result of a maze generation algorithm.
    MazeRenderer
    Renderer for a GraphMaze as a JavaFX GridPane
    MazeSerializationException
    Thrown when loading or saving a graph fails.
    MazeSolver
    Solves mazes with various algorithms.
    NewMazeDialogController
    Controller for the Maze Creation Dialog box (triggered when User clicks on "New" menu item)
    PlayArcadeDialogController
    The controller for the "play arcade" dialog.
    Player
    A player in a game session, moving around to maze to reach the end.
    PlayerInputSource
    Indicates which peripheral the player uses to move in the maze during a game.
    PlayerInputSource.Controller
    The player uses the n-th connected controller to move in the maze.
    PlayerInputSource.KeyboardArrows
    The player uses the keyboard with arrow keys to move in the maze.
    PlayerInputSource.KeyboardZQSD
    The player uses the keyboard with the ZQSD keys (AZERTY) to move in the maze.
    PlayerItemController
    The controller for a single player in the player list of the "play arcade dialog".
    PlayerProfile
    Contains all data for a player who's about to play a game: input settings and appearance.
    Point
    Point in a 2D space for mazes.
    Settings
    General settings for the app to remember across sessions
    SolveMazeController
    The controller for the "Solve Maze" dialog.
    SwiftnessHUDController
    The HUD controller for the swiftness game mode.
    Vector2
    A vector in 2D space, with double-precision floating point numbers.
